<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Iran-Australia,0096</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Report Says Australian Official Talks of Helping Rebuild Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEHRAN, Iran (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An official Iranian report said Australia's
foreign minister came to Iran on Wednesday ready to discuss his
nation's participation in Iran's post-war reconstruction.
   Foreign Minister Bill Hayden of Australia met with Iranian
President Ali Khamenei on Wednesday and called for more trade
between the two countries, the Islamic Republic News Agency said.
   It said Hayden expressed pleasure in the scheduled cease-fire in
the eight-year-old war between Iran and Iran. A U.N.-mediated truce
has been set for Aug. 20.
</TEXT>
