<1ST_LINE>u a AM-HelicopterCrash     08-10 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Helicopter Crash,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Injured, One Missing in Navy Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Navy helicopter crashed on a training mission
Wednesday off the Southern California coast, injuring three
crewmembers and triggering a search for the fourth man aboard,
officials said.
   The aircraft, a Sikorsky SH-2F assigned to Helicopter
Anti-submarine Squadron 35 at the North Island Naval Air Station in
San Diego, was about 35 miles south of San Clemente Island when it
crashed, the Navy said.
   Lt. j.g. Walter S. Hogan, 27, of Tucson, Ariz., was missing and
presumed lost at sea, the Navy said, but the search for him
continued.
   Lt. Mark S. Eoff, 33, of San Diego, was listed in critical
condition at Balboa Naval Hospital with unspecified injuries.
   Petty Officer 3rd Class John C. Santana, 22, of New York City
and Airman Steven P. Zelasco, 21, of Virginia, Minn., were both
listed in stable condition.
   The cause of the accident will be investigated, the Navy said.
</TEXT>
