<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--MatchmakerDebt     08-10 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Matchmaker Debt,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Judge Breaks Up Matchmaker's Marriage Fee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   You can't put a price on love and marriage, a judge
has ruled in declaring invalid a matchmaker's contract that
required a $250 bonus fee if her services led her clients to the
altar.
   Matchmaker Bobbie Heiman sued her customers, Denise Canchola and
Philip de Tournillion III, for the additional money following their
1984 marriage. She received $295 from each for arranging their
initial meeting in 1983.
   ``I was so disgusted at having to sue someone for getting
married and not paying the bonus,'' Ms. Heiman said. ``I got real
burned out matching people up and then not getting any strokes for
doing a good job.''
   But the couple, a nurse and a businessman, said they refused to
pay the fee out of principle and because mutual love, not Ms.
Heiman's magic, led them down the aisle.
   Dade County Judge Eli Breger on Monday agreed, declaring the
additional fee invalid.
</TEXT>
