<HEAD>Dutchmen Expelled For Lighting Cigarettes With Money</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Dutch tourists spotted lighting
cigarettes with Yugoslav money have been fined and expelled, the
state news agency Tanjug reported.
   In a report Tuesday, it identified the two as Peeters Hendrikus,
25, and Peeters Hermanus, 36, but gave no other details of the
incident in the Adriatic resort of Makarska.
   Yugoslavia's currency, the dinar, has fallen rapidly in value as
the country remains gripped by triple-digit inflation.
   With a dollar now worth around 3,000 dinars, and the largest
denomination note a 20,000 dinar bill, 100 dinar bills have become
virtually worthless.
</TEXT>
