<1ST_LINE>r a PM-ReaganLetter     08-10 0289</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Reagan Letter,0300</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bluefield Girl Gets Presidential Reply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLUEFIELD, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 10-year-old girl with plans to change
the world and an idea of how to do it sent President Reagan a poem
and pictures, and says she got back a letter of encouragement.
   But Nicole ``Nikki'' Lawrence says she still likes Democratic
presidential nominee Michael Dukakis for the top job _ until she's
old enough for it, that is.
   The Bluefield resident said she sent her July letter to Reagan
with drawings of national monuments, the president and his wife in
order to learn more about the job she wants to hold.
   ``Your letter reinforces my confidence that the United States
will remain strong, competitive, and free through the decades to
come, and may God bless you,'' Reagan wrote back, according to the
Bluefield Daily Telegraph.
   Nikki says she's wanted to be president since she was 3 years
old, and her platform is ready.
   ``You won't be paying so much taxes,'' she said. ``You're only
going to pay 10 cents a day in taxes.
   ``I have ways to stop water pollution, any other pollution. I'll
make a law against hair spray and spray-on deodorant to protect the
ozone layer.''
   In disarmament issues, Nikki said she would send every nuclear
warhead to Mars.
   Her 4-year-old brother, Michael, would be ``in charge of arms,''
while her father would be vice president and her mother would be
treasurer, she said.
   For now, however, Nikki says her vote goes to Dukakis, if only
he would improve his looks.
   ``He'd do better if he got Elvis sideburns,'' Nikki said. ``I
saw this show on Nickelodeon about Lincoln and his beard. They
showed how Dukakis would look if he got Elvis sideburns.''
</TEXT>
