<TEXT>
   A Massachusetts mother of a disabled child
says she told George Bush his proposed federal program for child
care is ``certainly a good beginning,'' but said she had some
questions as well.
   The vice president called Kathleen Mulligan, mother of a
2-year-old with Down's Syndrome, on Tuesday.
   The woman has worked for change in federal aid programs since
December 1986, when she was told her daughter was ineligible for
Supplemental Security Income payments while either the child or the
child's father lived at home care. Kenneth Mulligan earned more
