   ``My direct quote to the vice president was that this program is
certainly a good beginning,'' Mrs. Mulligan, 36, said of the phone
call.
   But Mrs. Mulligan said she remains wary because she has yet to
learn how the program will work. ``I asked for the cap to be lifted
so that it could affect all people nationwide,'' she said.
   She said she asked him a number of questions about how the
program would work. ``He said that when he returned to Washington
he would relay those questions to the proper people,'' she said.''
