<HEAD>Bush Iowa Campaign Head Predicts Midwesterner or Westerner on</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Ticket
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The best bet for the No. 2 spot on the
Republican ticket is a Westerner or Midwesterner and almost
certainly not a woman, George Bush's Iowa campaign manager predicts.
   And he said pairing Bush with former Republican presidential
rival Bob Dole would be the strongest ticket for Iowa.
   ``I think Bob Dole could probably do more to help the ticket in
Iowa than any other prospective vice presidential candidate,'' said
George Wittgraf. ``I think there's a good chance the ticket will
include a Midwesterner or a Westerner.''
   In any case, Wittgraf predicted, the second spot won't go to a
woman, because that would be viewed by voters as ``tokenism'' that
would hurt certain GOP nominee Bush.
   ``It would be viewed first as putting a woman on the ticket,''
Wittgraf said. ``Many people would view that as political tokenism.
She wouldn't be judged on her merits, she would be judged as a
woman.''
