<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla.: into October.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``It appears everything has gone well,'' said launch control
center commentator Hugh Harris. Officials hoped to have a
preliminary report on the ground-shaking firing within hours.
   At the end of a near-flawless countdown, the three main liquid
fuel engines at the base of the delta-winged spaceship flashed to
life. The launch pedestal was engulfed in a huge cloud of steam as
the fiery exhaust collided with tons of protective water pouring
over the foundation of the structure.
   Discovery's three 7,000-pound engines generated total thrust
equal to the energy output of 23 Hoover Dams as eight 3-foot-long
hardened steel bolts held the spaceship on the launch pad.
