<HEAD>Transit Pact OK'd in New Orleans; Strike During Convention Averted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The city's bus and streetcar drivers have
approved a new contract, averting a strike before next week's
Republican National Convention.
   The Amalgamated Transit Union said drivers approved the
three-year contract Tuesday. Vote totals were not released.
   The union represents more than 600 of the 700 bus and streetcar
drivers.
   Negotiators for the union and the Regional Transit Authority
reached a tentative agreement Sunday night, hours before a strike
deadline of 12:01 a.m. Monday.
   Top pay for drivers is now $10.10 an hour. Under the new
contract, that will rise in steps to $10.50 by 1991.
