<HEAD>Bentsen's Son, Daughter-in-law Said To Have $12.6 Million in Debts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A son of Sen. Lloyd Bentsen, the Democratic vice
presidential candidate, and his estranged wife have $12.6 million
in debts on their community property, according to court records in
the couple's divorce case.
   Lan C. Bentsen on Tuesday asked a judge to seal the file
involving his divorce from his wife, Lynne, The Houston Post
reported today. Bentsen said it had ``nothing'' to do with his
father being chosen as the running mate to Democratic presidential
nominee Michael Dukakis.
   He declined further comment, saying ``it's a personal matter.''
His attorney said any publicity about the case could harm the
couple's 8-year-old daughter, Skyler.
   Bentsen, 40, was sued for divorce last August by his wife, who
claims the 10-year-old marriage is insupportable due to marital
discord.
