in violation of a routine temporary divorce court order issued in
September 1987.
   Financial documents filed in the case indicate the couple's
community property, which includes Lan Bentsen's various real
estate interests, is $12.6 million in debt, the Post said. The
couple has about $4.5 million in assets and $17.2 million in
liabilities, according to documents.
   State District Judge John Montgomery granted the request to seal
the file, but said he would consider requests from organizations or
individuals that wished to see it. The Post was permitted to view
the documents.
   The divorce case is set for trial in February.
   Lan Bentsen, at one time president of Bath-Bentsen Interests,
was elected chairman of the board of Security National Bank in
1977. He has been doing campaigning for his father's Senate
re-election bid, which is being conducted along with Bentsen's
campaign with Dukakis for the White House.
