<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Fat Man,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Edelman Evicted, Goes to County Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESLEY HILLS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 800-pound man unable to get out of
bed was loaded by forklift onto a flatbed truck today, evicted from
his dilapidated bungalow.
   Michael Edelman was taken to a hospital until an apartment can
be renovated to accommodate the 24-year-old man too big to squeeze
through a regular-size doorway.
   Edelman, who had lived in the bungalow for two years with his
400-pound mother, Arlene, had put off eviction with court
challenges since April. His landlord wants to redevelop the
property in this suburb north of New York City.
   Edelman came to public attention in December when he fell out of
bed and had to be lifted up by a tow truck.
