<HEAD>One Good Turn Brings Another</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTAGE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One good turn deserves another, so this
small community is raising money to repay a Canadian disc jockey
who raised $12,000 to buy Portage a new police car.
   Radio station WWML owner Bill Henderson began the fund drive
Tuesday for Scruff Connors of St. Catharines, Ontario.
   The CHTZ-FM disc jockey was hospitalized while in Johnstown on
Friday after becoming ill at a restaurant. He hoped to be released
Tuesday but collapsed during a stress test and was scheduled for
heart treatment in Pittsburgh.
   ``First we wanted to raise money for his medical bills,''
Henderson said. ``But he said he didn't want that. We thought it
was a good idea to repay him for the loan he took out.''
   Connors, 20, took a personal loan to contribute to the patrol
car fund, which he organized after hearing that Portage was using a
dump truck for police patrols.
