<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Cher     08-10 0230</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Cher,0235</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cher Introduces New Perfume</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Like glamorous Sophia Loren, passionate
Elizabeth Taylor and elegant Gloria Vanderbilt, Cher has sniffed
the sweet smell of success, and she wants to share it with women
everywhere.
   Unveiling a luxury perfume that she helped develop and that
does, of course, bear her name, Cher appeared Wednesday at the
Plaza Hotel, wearing a black, skin-tight, off-the-shoulder
mini-dress by Bob Mackie, adorned with a peek-a-boo lace hem and
one lace sleeve.
   ``This is something new to me as a business,'' she said,
introducing ``Cher _ Uninhibited.''
   ``Uninhibited means something different to every one of us. .. .
It can suit every woman's idea of fantasy,'' said Cher, who added
that her own definition might be ``running naked through the park.''
   Michael Stern, president of Parfums Stern, said the fragrance
will be available around Nov. 1. Prices will range from $30 for a
1.7-ounce eau de toilette spray to $300 for a 1.7-ounce ``deluxe
perfume presentation.''
   Until now, Cher wore several perfumes simultaneously. She tried
out ``Uninhibited'' on friends during the testing, and her
boyfriend, Robert Camilletti, ``actually, finally liked it,'' she
said.
   ``When we first met ... I sprayed my perfume inside his leather
jacket and he said, `I can't stop thinking about you; I even smell
you.' And I thought, `It's a wicked trick, but it worked,''' she
confided.
</TEXT>
