<HEAD>Actress Killed in Auto Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jo Henderson, a stage and film actress who was
nominated for a Tony Award four years ago, has died in an
automobile accident in Chinle, Ariz. She was 54.
   The actress was driving to her home in Pomona, N.Y., from an
engagement in Southern California on Saturday when her car skidded
and collided with an oncoming vehicle, killing her instantly,
police said.
   Ms. Henderson appeared on Broadway and in many off-Broadway and
regional playhouse productions, including one in La Jolla, Calif.,
shortly before her death.
   Her performance in 1976 as the widowed mother of four young
daughters in ``Ladyhouse Blues,'' produced by the Phoenix Theater
Company won her an Obie Award. In 1984 she was nominated for a Tony
as best featured actress in ``Play Memory.''
   On screen, Ms. Henderson appeared in ``Lianna,'' a 1983 film by
John Sayles.
