further. But the timing of the increase caught many traders by
surprise.
   In one sense, analysts said, the Fed's action could turn out to
be a plus for the stock and bond markets if it achieves its stated
purpose of restraining inflation.
   But at the same time, it created problems for the stock market
by intensifying recession fears and adding to the allure of short
term interest-bearing investments, which compete with stocks and
bonds for investors' favor.
