<HEAD>Woolworth Earnings Up 16 Percent in 2nd Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   F.W. Woolworth Co. reported Wednesday its
second-quarter earnings rose 16 percent as the retailer's sales
increased 13 percent.
   Woolworth said it earned $43 million, or 68 cents per share, up
from $37 million, or 56 cents per share, in the second quarter of
last year.
   The company said its sales increased to $1.84 billion during the
quarter, compared with $1.63 billion a year earlier.
   The sales gain was helped in part by currency fluctuations, the
company said.
   For the first half, Woolworth said it earned $78 million, or
$1.22 per share, up 18 percent from $66 million, or 99 cents per
share, in the first six months of 1987.
   First-half sales rose to $3.55 billion from $3.16 billion.
