<HEAD>Affiliated Reports $10.5 Million Second Quarter Net Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Affiliated Publications Inc., publisher of the
Boston Globe, reported Wednesday that it lost $10.5 million during
the second quarter of this year, due to its share of losses by
McCaw Cellular Communications Inc.
   In the same period last year, Affiliated posted a profit of
$72.8 million, or $1.03 per share. The year-earlier period
reflected Affiliated's $39.9 million share of gains from the sale
of discontinued McCaw operations and its $17.9 million share of a
one-time credit.
   Second quarter revenue rose to $140.4 million from $125.9
million in the year-earlier period.
   The company said its share of losses in McCaw Cellular
Communications Inc. reduced its net income by $26.5 million for the
quarter.
   Affiliated reported second quarter income from consolidated
operations _ which does not include the impact of charges from of
its invsetment in McCaw _ of $16 million, down 6 percent from the
same period last year.
   The company now owns more than 61.5 million shares of common
stock in MCCI, the nation's largest cellular telephone systems
operator.
   For the first six months of the year, Affiliated reported losses
of $24.8 million on revenue of $267.1 million. That compared with
net earnings of $81.5 million, or 34 cents a share, on revenue of
$228.7 million in the first six months of last year.
</TEXT>
