in percentage terms, total hundreds of millions of dollars, the
Pentagon says.
   An unusually broad internal defense audit found that nearly half
the contracts reviewed involved some measure of overcharging,
auditors reported Tuesday.
   In the majority of instances, the overcharges resulted from a
military contractor's failure to abide by a law requiring the
company to share with the government the latest information it has
on labor and material costs.
